            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20909",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jsahleen",
                        "name": "jsahleen",
                        "displayName": "Joel Sahleen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "this is a non-issue. Turns out I was following the old Zend Controller documentation which suggested that controller names needed to be camelCased. However, because the dispatcher dynamically constructs controller file names using an initial capital, camel cased controller names will not work on case-sensitive systems. It might be good to make a note in the current documentation about this. It should be specified that controller names need to start with a capital.\n\nSorry about the red herring.\n\nJ.",
